c: 3
v: 167
t: "and know those who acted hypocritically.\" When they were told, \"Come, fight in God's cause and defend yourselves,\" they replied, \"If we knew that fighting would take place, we would surely follow you.\" They were that day nearer to unbelief than to belief. The words they utter bear no relation to what is in their hearts. God knows well what they conceal"